{
  "doc_id": "1704",
  "text": "The advent of molecular-based methods for identifying and characterizing microorganisms has led to a new era of microbial discovery. The 16S rDNA-based techniques have been proven to be more substantially sensitive and accurate than traditional techniques that depend on microbial culture [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Several studies have evaluated the presence of multiple and diverse bacterial 16S rDNA sequences in prostate biopsy tissue from BPH and PC patients [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . In the present study, we used PCR-DGGE with 16S rDNA finger printing analysis to investigate bacterial composition in the biopsy of PC patients in the PSA grey-zone with or without hypertension.",
